===Etymology===
Middle English < Old English [[sunu]] < Proto-Germanic '''*sunuz''' < Proto-Indo-European '''*sunu-'''/'''*sunyu-''' < PIE root '''*su-''' (to give birth).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/sʌn/}}, {{SAMPA|/sVn/}}
* {{audio|en-us-son.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ʌn}}

====Homophones====
